mpics]]\n|-\n|width=10px bgcolor=#ffffcc| ||Team qualified for the 1989 World Men's Handball Championship Group B\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Rank!!width=170|Team\n|-bgcolor=#ccffcc\n|align=center|[[File:gold medal icon.svg]]||{{hb|ALG}}\n|-bgcolor=#ffffcc\n|align=center|[[File:silver medal icon.svg]]||{{hb|EGY}}\n|-\n|align=center|[[File:bronze medal icon.svg]]||{{hb|TUN|1959}}\n|-\n|align=center|4||{{hb|CGO|1970}}\n|-\n|align=center|5||{{hb|ANG}}\n|-\n|align=center|6||{{hb|CIV}}\n|-\n|align=center|7||{{hb|SEN}}\n|-\n|align=center|8||{{hb|MAR}}\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{African Handball Championship}}\n\n[[Category:African handball championships]]\n[[Category:International sports competitions hosted by Morocco|Handball]]\n[[Category:1987 in handball|A]]\n[[Category:1987 in Moroccan sport|Handball]]\n[[Category:Handball in Morocco]]\n[[Category:20th century in Rabat]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Morocco]]\n[[Category:July 1987 sports events in Africa]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox International Handball Competition\n| tourney_name   = African Men's Championship\n| year           = 1987\n| yearr          = \n| other_titles   = \n| image          = \n| size           = \n| caption        = \n| country        = Morocco\n| dates          = 3 \u2013 12 July\n| num_teams      = 8\n| confederations = 1\n| venues         = 1\n| cities         = 1\n| champion       = ALG\n| count          = 4\n| second         = EGY\n| third          = TUN\n| third-flagvar  = 1959\n| fourth         = CGO\n| fourth-flagvar = 1970\n| matches        = \n| goals          = \n| attendance     = \n| top_scorer     = \n| player         = \n| previous       = 1985 African Men's Handball Championship\n| next           = 1989 African Men's Handball Championship\n}}\n\nThe '''1987 African Men's Handball Championship''', was held in [[Rabat]], [[Morocco]], from 3 to 12 July 1987. It acted as the African qualifying tournament for the [[Handball at the 1988 Summer Olympics|1988 Summer Olympics]] in [[Seoul]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.todor66.com/handball/Africa/Men_1987.html |title=Men Handball VII Africa Championship 1987 Morocco |work=todor66.com |publisher=Todor Krastev |date=November 26, 2016 |accessdate= }}</ref>\n\nIn the final, [[Algeria national handball team|Algeria]] win their fourth consecutive title beating [[Egypt national handball team|Egypt]] in the final game.\n\n==Qualified teams==\n{{col-start}}{{col-2}}\n*{{hb|ALG}}\n*{{hb|ANG}}\n*{{hb|CGO|1970}}\n*{{hb|EGY}}\n{{col-2}}\n*{{hb|CIV}}\n*{{hb|MAR}} ''{{small|(hosts)}}''\n*{{hb|SEN}}\n*{{hb|TUN|1959}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Squads==\n{{Main article|1987 African Men's Handball Championship squads}}\n\n==Group stage==\n{{Expand section|date=August 2017}}\n''All times are local ([[UTC+01:00|UTC+1]]).''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"|&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n|Team advance to the knockout stage\n|}\n\n===Group A===\n{{Handball table start}}\n{{hbt-row |team={{hb|ALG}} |bg=a |w=3 |d=0 |l=0 |gf=78 |ga=55}}\n{{hbt-row |team={{hb|EGY}} |bg=a |w=0 |d=0 |l=0 |gf=0  |ga=0 }}\n{{hbt-row |team={{hb|CIV}} |bg=  |w=0 |d=0 |l=0 |gf=0  |ga=0 }}\n{{hbt-row |team={{hb|MAR}} |bg=  |w=0 |d=0 |l=0 |gf=0  |ga=0 }}\n{{Handball table end}}\n\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 3 July 1987\n|time    = \n|team1   = {{hb-rt|ALG}}\n|score   = 23 \u2013 16\n|team2   = {{hb|MAR}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = \n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = [[Rabat]]\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n----\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 5 July 1987\n|time    = \n|team1   = {{hb-rt|ALG}}\n|score   = 22 \u2013 12\n|team2   = {{hb|EGY}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = \n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = [[Rabat]]\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n----\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 7 July 1987\n|time    = \n|team1   = {{hb-rt|ALG}}\n|score   = 33 \u2013 27\n|team2   = 