{"title_page": "Chiefdom of Mangshi", "text_new": "{{Infobox country\n|native_name= \u8292\u5e02\u571f\u53f8\n|conventional_long_name= Chiefdom of Mangshi\n|common_name= Chiefdom of Mangshi\n|era= \n|status= [[Tusi|Native Chiefdom]] of China\n|year_start= 1443\n|year_end= 1955\n|life_span= \n|p1= Mong Mao\n|flag_p1=\n|p2 = \n|flag_p2 = \n|s1 = People's Republic of China\n|flag_s1 =\n|s2= \n|flag_s2 = \n|image_flag=\n|image_coat = \n|coa_size = \n|image_map = \u8292\u5e02\u571f\u53f8\u7586\u57df.jpg\n|image_map_caption = Territory in modern [[Yunnan]]\n|flag = \n|capital= [[Mangshi]]\n|common_languages= [[Tai Nuea language]]\n|government_type = [[Monarchy]]\n|title_leader = Tusi\n|leader1 = Fang Dingzheng {{small|(first)}}\n|year_leader1 = 1443\u20131459\n|leader2 = Fang Yulong {{small|(last)}}\n|year_leader2 = 1948\u20131955\n|religion= \n|currency=\n|today = {{flag|China}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Chiefdom of Mangshi''', officially '''Mangshi ''Yuyi Zhangguansi''''' and '''Mangshi ''Anfusi''''' was a [[Dai people|Dai]] autonomous [[Tusi]] chiefdom in the west of [[Yunnan]], [[China]] from 1443 to 1955. In 1443, [[Ming dynasty]] established Mangshi ''Yuyi Zhangguansi'' ({{lang|zh|\u8292\u5e02\u5fa1\u5937\u957f\u5b98\u53f8}}) because Mangshi chief made a contribution in [[Luchuan\u2013Pingmian campaigns]], and then upgraded to Mangshi ''Anfusi'' ({{lang|zh|\u8292\u5e02\u5b89\u629a\u53f8}}) in 1640. Chiefdom of Mangshi has an absolute dictatorship in politics, military, economy at the territory, and use the rule of [[primogeniture]].<ref name=\"\u6f5e\u897f\u53bf\u5fd7\">{{cite book |author=\u4e91\u5357\u7701\u6f5e\u897f\u53bf\u5fd7\u7f16\u7e82\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a |date=1993 |script-title=zh:\u6f5e\u897f\u53bf\u5fd7 |trans-title=Annals of Luxi County |language=Chinese |location=[[Kunming]] |publisher=Yunnan Education Publishing House |isbn=7-5415-0685-0}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]] period, the central government used many of method try to abolish chiefdom of Mangshi, for example, established a direct control government \"Luxi Administrate Bureau\" ({{lang|zh|\u6f5e\u897f\u8bbe\u6cbb\u5c40}}).<ref name=\"\u6f5e\u897f\u53bf\u5fd7\"/> But chiefdom of Mangshi associate with other chiefdoms to counteractant the abolishment. At its worst, chiefdoms had a consideration for independence from China. Finally, the central government compromised with chiefdoms.<ref>{{cite journal |author=\u738b\u6625\u6865 |title=\u571f\u53f8\u5b58\u5e9f\u4e0e\u56fd\u5bb6\u7edf\u4e00(1944~1948) |trans-title=Maintenance or abolishment of Tusi chieftain system and unification of China (1944-1948) |language=Chinese |journal=Journal of Yunnan Minzu University (Social Sciences) |date=2015 |volume=32 |issue=1 |pages=103\u2013108 |doi=10.13727/j.cnki.53-1191/c.2015.01.015 }}</ref>\n\nAfter [[People's Republic of China]] controlled this area, the central government initiated the [[Chinese Land Reform|Chinese Land Reform Movement]]. Chiefdom of Mangshi lost his power and land, finally abolished in 1955.<ref>{{cite book |author=\u5fb7\u5b8f\u53f2\u5fd7\u7f16\u59d4\u4f1a\u529e\u516c\u5ba4 |script-title=zh:\u5fb7\u5b8f\u53f2\u5fd7\u8d44\u6599 \u7b2c\u4e03\u96c6 |trans-title=Annals material of Dehong, Volume 7 |language=Chinese |location=[[Mangshi]] |publisher=Dehong Nationalities Publishing House |date=1986 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Shan states}}\n\n[[Category:Tusi]]\n[[Category:History of Yunnan]]\n[[Category:Mangshi]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in the 15th century]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in the 20th century]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox country\n|native_name= \u8292\u5e02\u571f\u53f8\n|conventional_long_name= Chiefdom of Mangshi\n|common_name= Chiefdom of Mangshi\n|era= \n|status= [[Tusi|Native Chiefdom]] of China\n|year_start= 1443\n|year_end= 1955\n|life_span= \n|p1= Mong Mao\n|flag_p1=\n|p2 = \n|flag_p2 = \n|s1 = People's Republic of China\n|flag_s1 =\n|s2= \n|flag_s2 = \n|image_flag=\n|image_coat = \n|coa_size = \n|image_map = \u8292\u5e02\u571f\u53f8\u7586\u57df.jpg\n|image_map_caption = Territory in modern [[Yunnan]]\n|flag = \n|capital= [[Mangshi]]\n|common_languages= [[Tai Nuea language]]\n|government_type = [[Monarchy]]\n|title_leader = Tusi\n|leader1 = Fang Dingzheng {{small|(first)}}\n|year_leader1 = 1443\u20131459\n|leader2 = Fang Yulong {{small|(last)}}\n|year_leader2 = 1948\u20131955\n|religion= \n|currency=\n|today = {{flag|China}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Chiefdom of Mangshi''', officially '''Mangshi ''Yuyi Zhangguansi''''' and '''Mangshi ''Anfusi''''' was a [[Dai people|Dai]] autonomous [[Tusi]] chiefdom in the west of [[Yunnan]], [[China]] from 1443 to 1955. In 1443, [[Ming dynasty]] established Mangshi ''Yuyi Zhangguansi'' ({{lang|zh|\u8292\u5e02\u5fa1\u5937\u957f\u5b98\u53f8}}) because Mangshi chief made a contribution in [[Luchuan\u2013Pingmian campaigns]], and then upgraded to Mangshi ''Anfusi'' ({{lang|zh|\u8292\u5e02\u5b89\u629a\u53f8}}) in 1640. Chiefdom of Mangshi has an absolute dictatorship in politics, military, economy at the territory, and use the rule of [[primogeniture]].<ref name=\"\u6f5e\u897f\u53bf\u5fd7\">{{cite book |author=\u4e91\u5357\u7701\u6f5e\u897f\u53bf\u5fd7\u7f16\u7e82\u59d4\u5458\u4f1a |date=1993 |script-title=zh:\u300a\u6f5e\u897f\u53bf\u5fd7\u300b |trans-title=Annals of Luxi County |language=Chinese |location=[[Kunming]] |publisher=Yunnan Education Publishing House |isbn=7-5415-0685-0}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]] period, the central government used many of method try to abolish chiefdom of Mangshi, for example, established a direct control government \"Luxi Administrate Bureau\" ({{lang|zh|\u6f5e\u897f\u8bbe\u6cbb\u5c40}}).<ref name=\"\u6f5e\u897f\u53bf\u5fd7\"/> But chiefdom of Mangshi associate with other chiefdoms to counteractant the abolishment. At its worst, chiefdoms had a consideration for independence from China. Finally, the central government compromised with chiefdoms.<ref>{{cite journal |author=\u738b\u6625\u6865 |title=\u571f\u53f8\u5b58\u5e9f\u4e0e\u56fd\u5bb6\u7edf\u4e00(1944~1948) |trans-title=Maintenance or abolishment of Tusi chieftain system and unification of China (1944-1948) |language=Chinese |journal=Journal of Yunnan Minzu University (Social Sciences) |date=2015 |volume=32 |issue=1 |pages=103\u2013108 |doi=10.13727/j.cnki.53-1191/c.2015.01.015 }}</ref>\n\nAfter [[People's Republic of China]] controlled this area, the central government initiated the [[Chinese Land Reform|Chinese Land Reform Movement]]. Chiefdom of Mangshi lost his power and land, finally abolished in 1955.<ref>{{cite book |author=\u5fb7\u5b8f\u53f2\u5fd7\u7f16\u59d4\u4f1a\u529e\u516c\u5ba4 |title=\u5fb7\u5b8f\u53f2\u5fd7\u8d44\u6599 \u7b2c\u4e03\u96c6 |trans-title=Annals material of Dehong, Volume 7 |language=Chinese |location=[[Mangshi]] |publisher=Dehong Nationalities Publishing House |date=1986 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Shan states}}\n\n[[Category:Tusi]]\n[[Category:History of Yunnan]]\n[[Category:Mangshi]]\n[[Category:States and territories established in the 15th century]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in the 20th century]]\n", "name_user": "\u745e\u4e3d\u6c5f\u7684\u6cb3\u6c34", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chiefdom_of_Mangshi"}
{"title_page": "1989 African Men's Handball Championship", "text_new": "{{Infobox International Handball Competition\n| tourney_name   = African Men's Championship\n| year           = 1989\n| yearr          = \n| other_titles   = \n| image          = \n| size           = \n| caption        = \n| country        = Algeria\n| dates          = 17 \u2013 27 July\n| num_teams      = 7\n| confederations = 1\n| venues         = 1\n| cities         = 1\n| champion       = ALG\n| count          = 5\n| second         = EGY\n| third          = TUN\n| third-flagvar  = 1959\n| fourth         = CGO\n| fourth-flagvar = 1970\n| matches        = \n| goals          = \n| attendance     = \n| top_scorer     = \n| player         = \n| previous       = 1987 African Men's Handball Championship\n| next           = 1991 African Men's Handball Championship\n}}\n\nThe '''1989 African Men's Handball Championship''', was held in [[Algiers]], [[Algeria]], from 17 to 27 July 1989. It acted as the African qualifying tournament for the [[1990 World Men's Handball Championship|1990 World Championship]] in [[Czechoslovakia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.todor66.com/handball/Africa/Men_1989.html |title=Men Handball VIII Africa Championship 1989 - Algeria |work=todor66.com |publisher=Todor Krastev |date=November 26, 2016 |accessdate= }}</ref>\n\nIn the final, [[Algeria national handball team|Algeria]] win their fifth consecutive title beating [[Egypt national handball team|Egypt]] in the final game 18\u201317.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dzairsports.com/2016/01/04/handball-can-2016-historique-des-confrontations-egypt-algerie |title=Historique des confrontations Alg\u00e9rie \u2013 Egypt |work=dZAIRSports.com |publisher=Admin |date=January 4, 2016 |accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n==Qualified teams==\n{{col-start}}{{col-2}}\n*{{hb|ALG}} ''{{small|(hosts)}}''\n*{{hb|ANG}}\n*{{hb|CGO|1970}}\n*{{hb|EGY}}\n{{col-2}}\n*{{hb|CIV}}\n*{{hb|MAR}}\n*{{hb|TUN|1959}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Squads==\n{{Main article|1989 African Men's Handball Championship squads}}\n\n==Group stage==\n{{Expand section|date=August 2017}}\n''All times are local ([[UTC+01:00|UTC+1]]).''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"|&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n|Team advance to the knockout stage\n|}\n\n===Group A===\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|winpoints=2\n|show_positions=n\n\n|team1=ALG|name_ALG={{hb|ALG}}\n|team2=TUN|name_TUN={{hb|TUN|1959}}\n|team3=MAR|name_MAR={{hb|MAR}}\n|team4=ANG|name_ANG={{hb|ANG}}\n|win_ALG=3|draw_ALG=0|loss_ALG=0|gf_ALG=66|ga_ALG=50\n|win_TUN=0|draw_TUN=0|loss_TUN=0|gf_TUN=0|ga_TUN=0\n|win_MAR=0|draw_MAR=0|loss_MAR=0|gf_MAR=0|ga_MAR=0\n|win_ANG=0|draw_ANG=0|loss_ANG=0|gf_ANG=0|ga_ANG=0\n\n|col_A=green1|text_A=\n|result1=A|result2=A\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 17 July 1989\n|time    = \n|team1   = {{hb-rt|ALG}}\n|score   = 19 \u2013 11\n|team2   = {{hb|MAR}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = \n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = [[Hac\u00e8ne Harcha Arena|Harcha Arena]], [[Algiers]]\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n----\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 19 July 1989\n|time    = \n|team1   = {{hb-rt|ALG}}\n|score   = 18 \u2013 16\n|team2   = {{hb|TUN}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = \n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = [[Hac\u00e8ne Harcha Arena|Harcha Arena]], [[Algiers]]\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n----\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 21 July 1989\n|time    = \n|team1   = {{hb-rt|ALG}}\n|score   = 29 \u2013 23\n|team2   = {{hb|ANG}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = \n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = [[Hac\u00e8ne Harcha Arena|Harcha Arena]], [[Algiers]]\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n\n===Group B===\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|winpoints=2\n|show_positions=n\n\n|team1=EGY|name_EGY={{hb|EGY}}\n|team2=CGO|name_CGO={{hb|CGO|1970}}\n|team3=CIV|name_CIV={{hb|CIV}}\n|win_EGY=0|draw_EGY=0|loss_EGY=0|gf_EGY=0|ga_EGY=0\n|win_CGO=0|draw_CGO=0|loss_CGO=0|gf_CGO=0|ga_CGO=0\n|win_CIV=0|draw_CIV=0|loss_CIV=0|gf_CIV=0|ga_CIV=0\n\n|col_A=green1|text_A=\n|result1=A|result2=A\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n==Knockout stage==\n{{#invoke:RoundN|N4\n|widescore=yes|bold_winner=high\n|3rdplace=yes\n|RD1=Semifinals\n|RD2=Final\n|Consol=Third place\n<!-- Date-Place/Team 1/Score 1/Team 2/Score 2 -->\n<!-- semi finals -->\n| July \u2013 [[Algiers]]|{{hb|ALG}}|18|{{hb|CGO|1970}}|13\n| July \u2013 [[Algiers]]|'''{{hb|EGY}}'''| |{{hb|TUN|1959}}|\n<!-- final -->\n| 27 July \u2013 [[Algiers]]|{{hb|ALG}}|18|{{hb|EGY}}|17\n<!-- third place -->\n| July \u2013 [[Algiers]]|{{hb|CGO|1970}}| |'''{{hb|TUN|1959}}'''|\n}}\n\n===Semifinals===\n{{handballbox\n|date    = ... July 1989\n|time    = \n|team1   = {{hb-rt|ALG}}\n|score   = 18 \u2013 13\n|team2   = {{hb|CGO|1970}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = \n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = [[Hac\u00e8ne Harcha Arena|Harcha Arena]], [[Algiers]]\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n----\n{{handballbox\n|date    = ... July 1989\n|time    = \n|team1   = {{hb-rt|EGY}}\n|score   = \u2013\n|team2   = {{hb|TUN|1959}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = \n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = [[Hac\u00e8ne Harcha Arena|Harcha Arena]], [[Algiers]]\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n\n===Third place game===\n{{handballbox\n|date    = ... July 1989\n|bg      = #cc9966\n|time    = \n|team1   = {{hb-rt|CGO|1970}}\n|score   = \u2013\n|team2   = {{hb|TUN|1959}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = \n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = [[Hac\u00e8ne Harcha Arena|Harcha Arena]], [[Algiers]]\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n\n===Final===\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 27 July 1989\n|bg      = gold\n|time    = \n|team1   = {{hb-rt|ALG}}\n|score   = 18 \u2013 17\n|team2   = {{hb|EGY}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = \n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = [[Hac\u00e8ne Harcha Arena|Harcha Arena]], [[Algiers]]\n|attendance = 8 000\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n\n==Final ranking==\n{| class=\"infobox bordered\"\n|-\n|width=10px bgcolor=#ccffcc| ||Team qualified for the [[1990 World Men's Handball Championship|1990 World Championship]]\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Rank!!width=170|Team\n|-bgcolor=#ccffcc\n|align=center|[[File:gold medal icon.svg]]||{{hb|ALG}}\n|-\n|align=center|[[File:silver medal icon.svg]]||{{hb|EGY}}\n|-\n|align=center|[[File:bronze medal icon.svg]]||{{hb|TUN|1959}}\n|-\n|align=center|4||{{hb|CGO|1970}}\n|-\n|align=center|5||{{hb|MAR}}\n|-\n|align=center|6||{{hb|CIV}}\n|-\n|align=center|7||{{hb|ANG}}\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{African Handball Championship}}\n\n[[Category:African handball championships]]\n[[Category:International sports competitions hosted by Algeria|Handball]]\n[[Category:1989 in handball|A]]\n[[Category:1989 in Algerian sport|Handball]]\n[[Category:Handball in Algeria]]\n[[Category:20th century in Algiers]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Algeria]]\n[[Category:July 1989 sports events in Africa]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox International Handball Competition\n| tourney_name   = African Men's Championship\n| year           = 1989\n| yearr          = \n| other_titles   = \n| image          = \n| size           = \n| caption        = \n| country        = Algeria\n| dates          = 17 \u2013 27 July\n| num_teams      = 7\n| confederations = 1\n| venues         = 1\n| cities         = 1\n| champion       = ALG\n| count          = 5\n| second         = EGY\n| third          = TUN\n| third-flagvar  = 1959\n| fourth         = CGO\n| fourth-flagvar = 1970\n| matches        = \n| goals          = \n| attendance     = \n| top_scorer     = \n| player         = \n| previous       = 1987 African Men's Handball Championship\n| next           = 1991 African Men's Handball Championship\n}}\n\nThe '''1989 African Men's Handball Championship''', was held in [[Algiers]], [[Algeria]], from 17 to 27 July 1989. It acted as the African qualifying tournament for the [[1990 World Men's Handball Championship|1990 World Championship]] in [[Czechoslovakia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.todor66.com/handball/Africa/Men_1989.html |title=Men Handball VIII Africa Championship 1989 - Algeria |work=todor66.com |publisher=Todor Krastev |date=November 26, 2016 |accessdate= }}</ref>\n\nIn the final, [[Algeria national handball team|Algeria]] win their fifth consecutive title beating [[Egypt national handball team|Egypt]] in the final game 18\u201317.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dzairsports.com/2016/01/04/handball-can-2016-historique-des-confrontations-egypt-algerie |title=Historique des confrontations Alg\u00e9rie \u2013 Egypt |work=dZAIRSports.com |publisher=Admin |date=January 4, 2016 |accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n==Qualified teams==\n{{col-start}}{{col-2}}\n*{{hb|ALG}} ''{{small|(hosts)}}''\n*{{hb|ANG}}\n*{{hb|CGO|1970}}\n*{{hb|EGY}}\n{{col-2}}\n*{{hb|CIV}}\n*{{hb|MAR}}\n*{{hb|TUN|1959}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Squads==\n{{Main article|1989 African Men's Handball Championship squads}}\n\n==Group stage==\n{{Expand section|date=August 2017}}\n''All times are local ([[UTC+01:00|UTC+1]]).''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"|&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n|Team advance to the knockout stage\n|}\n\n===Group A===\n{{Handball table start}}\n{{hbt-row |team={{hb|ALG}}      |bg=a |w=3 |d=0 |l=0 |gf=66|ga=50}}\n{{hbt-row |team={{hb|TUN|1959}} |bg=a |w=0 |d=0 |l=0 |gf=0 |ga=0 }}\n{{hbt-row |team={{hb|MAR}}      |bg=  |w=0 |d=0 |l=0 |gf=0 |ga=0 }}\n{{hbt-row |team={{hb|ANG}}      |bg=  |w=0 |d=0 |l=0 |gf=0 |ga=0 }}\n{{Handball table end}}\n\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 17 July 1989\n|t